{# Values read from the pricing plan (DB, editable in the Console; falls back to constants). #}
{% set plan = plan_tarifaire() %}
{% set readWeight = plan.readWeight %}
{% set freeAllowance = plan.freeAllowance|number_format(0, '.', ',') %}
{% set freeWindowHours = plan.freeWindowHours %}

<p class="cgu-intro">
    On JS Brokers, the <strong>token</strong> is the unit measuring your usage of the platform.
    It enables fair, pay-as-you-go pricing while keeping a renewable <strong>free tier</strong>
    to get started and work day to day.
</p>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>1. What is a token?</h2>
    <p>
        A token measures the volume of data exchanged between your browser and our servers.
        Each operation "weighs" a number of tokens, deducted from your balance.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>2. When are tokens consumed?</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Output (reading)</strong>: every entity displayed/downloaded to your screen costs <strong>{{ readWeight }} tokens</strong>. Loading a list of 20 items therefore costs 20 × {{ readWeight }} = {{ 20 * readWeight }} tokens.</li>
        <li><strong>Input (writing)</strong>: every save (creation or update) costs a variable weight depending on the entity type.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>3. Entity weights on write</h2>
    <table class="cgu-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Entity</th><th>Weight (tokens)</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            {% for fqcn, poids in plan.writeWeights %}
            <tr><td>{{ token_entite_label(fqcn, 'en') }}</td><td>{{ poids }}</td></tr>
            {% endfor %}
            <tr><td>Any other entity</td><td>{{ plan.defaultWriteWeight }}</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Read (per entity, output)</td><td>{{ readWeight }}</td></tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>4. The free tier (Basic)</h2>
    <p>
        Every account receives <strong>{{ freeAllowance }} free tokens</strong>, automatically
        <strong>renewed every {{ freeWindowHours }} hours</strong>. The counter starts on your first activity after
        account creation. Free tokens do not accumulate: at each renewal, the free balance is
        reset to {{ freeAllowance }}.
    </p>
    <p>
        To get started friction-free, <strong>creating your very first company is free</strong>:
        no tokens are charged during the welcome assistant. Additional companies are then billed
        at the usual weight (see the table above).
    </p>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>5. Prepaid packs</h2>
    <p>Need more? You can buy <strong>stackable</strong> packs:</p>
    <table class="cgu-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Pack</th><th>Price</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
            {% for key, p in plan.packs %}
            <tr><td>{{ p.label|default(key|capitalize) }} — {{ p.tokens|number_format(0, '.', ',') }} tokens</td><td>${{ p.price }}</td></tr>
            {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
        Prepaid tokens are consumed first; once depleted, you automatically fall back to the
        free tier ({{ freeAllowance }} tokens / {{ freeWindowHours }} h).
    </p>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>6. What happens when tokens run out?</h2>
    <p>
        When your balance (free + prepaid) is no longer enough, <strong>reading and writing are
        temporarily blocked</strong>. You can then either <strong>top up</strong> a pack or
        <strong>wait for the next renewal</strong> of your free allowance (within {{ freeWindowHours }} hours).
    </p>
</section>

<section class="cgu-section">
    <h2>7. Who pays and who consumes?</h2>
    <p>
        The <strong>company owner</strong> pays. Any activity performed within a company — by its
        owner <em>or</em> by invited collaborators — is deducted from that company owner's balance.
    </p>
</section>
